    "view": {
      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<p><strong>Points</strong> primitive is intended to be used for small particles such as sparks, snowflakes, or raindrops. They are optimized for the case where the intended particle is small, taking up at most a couple of pixels on the screen.</p><h4 id=\"Particles-TypesofPoints\">Types of Points</h4><ul><li><p>Points with normals are rendered as disks.</p></li><li><p>Points without normals: these are modeled as small spheres. These are real spheres that can be reflective and/or refractive. They can be used to model small water droplets though you should be aware that path tracing a large number of refractive droplets can be very costly.</p></li></ul><p>The width of the points is defined in the current object coordinate system and defaults to 1.0. You can specify either a single width value for all points using the <strong>&quot;constantwidth&quot;</strong> parameter, which is defined as a constant float, or give individual points separate widths by using the varying float variable <strong>&quot;width&quot;</strong>.</p><h4 id=\"Particles-Examples\">Examples</h4><p>Points are nearly ideal for generating star fields. The following image consists of about five thousand stars, randomly colored.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"997\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542213120/stars.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330463761&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=511&amp;height=258\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/542213120/stars.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330463761&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"258\" data-width=\"511\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"542213141\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"stars.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"542213120\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"8e16cf8e-7968-4300-974c-2eb09bd2a2e6\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542213120/stars.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330463761&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=511&amp;height=258 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542213120/stars.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330463761&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=511&amp;height=258 1x\"></span><p>Points may be motion-blurred as well. In this picture, the camera has been rotated to generate a picture reminiscent of star trails.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"997\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542213120/blurstars.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330463761&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=511&amp;height=258\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/542213120/blurstars.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330463761&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"258\" data-width=\"511\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"542213144\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"blurstars.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"542213120\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"6b73c7ba-f803-4407-ac2b-dab1015a2196\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542213120/blurstars.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330463761&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=511&amp;height=258 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542213120/blurstars.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330463761&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=511&amp;height=258 1x\"></span><p>You can also create fire or explosion effects using points as shown below. Here a particle system was used to generate one hundred thousand particles originating from four sources. The shader sets the opacity to 0 causing the particle intensities to accumulate. At the center of an explosion where many particles overlap this gives the illusion of a glowing hot center.<br/></p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"997\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542213120/fountain.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330463519&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=605&amp;height=304\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/542213120/fountain.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330463519&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"304\" data-width=\"605\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"542213138\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"fountain.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"542213120\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"cd809368-93d1-4e5e-a9cd-3d73cf1750ce\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542213120/fountain.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330463519&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=605&amp;height=304 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542213120/fountain.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330463519&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=605&amp;height=304 1x\"></span>"
    }
